No matter how hard it is to uninstall Oracle, it is still much easier than installing it.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
It seems that Oracle intentionally makes it really hard to install/uninstall its products - perhaps because it wants those certified Oracle engineers to get contracts.

There is nothing easier than removing Oracle from Windows box. Hmm... Actually, I&#039;m wrong. It&#039;s even easier on Unix.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Anyway, if a OUI doesn&#039;t work the way you expected then stop all remaining Oracle services, remove directory where Oracle was installed. Then remove registry keys under HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESOFTWAREORACLE. If you have any Oracle services left then remove them under HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESYSTEMCurrentControlSetServices. Restart your computer. Done.

I got a reply from Tim Ford &quot; Its easier to just rebuild the server.&quot;&lt;br /&gt;
